{"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef","doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)"},"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"addToggleRef"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"data"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil)"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This functionality is intended for binding "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":" to a proxy"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"object managed by another memory manager. This is done with two","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"paired references: the strong reference added by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"text":" and a reverse reference to the proxy","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object which is either a strong reference or weak reference."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The setup is that when there are no other references to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"only a weak reference is held in the reverse direction from "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the proxy object, but when there are other references held to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"object"},{"type":"text","text":", a strong reference is held. The "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" callback is called"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"when the reference from "},{"code":"object","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to the proxy object should be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"“toggled” from strong to weak ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"is_last_ref"},{"type":"text","text":" true) or weak to strong"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"is_last_ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" false)."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Since a (normal) reference must be held to the object before","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"calling ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", the initial state of the reverse"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"link is always strong.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Multiple toggle references may be added to the same gobject,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"however if there are multiple toggle references to an object, none"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of them will ever be notified until all but one are removed.  For"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"this reason, you should only ever use a toggle reference if there"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is important state in the proxy object."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if you unref the object on another thread, then "},{"code":"notify","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" might","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"still be invoked after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":", and the object argument"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might be a dangling pointer. If the object is destroyed on other threads,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"you must take care of that yourself."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_add_toggle_ref()"},{"type":"text","text":" must be released with "},{"code":"g_object_remove_toggle_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10GLibObject0B8ProtocolPAAE12addToggleRef6notify4datayySvSg_SpySo8_GObjectVGSgs5Int32VtXCSg_AGtF::SYNTHESIZED::s:10GLibObject14SignalGroupRefV","symbolKind":"method","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"notify","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","text":"GToggleNotify"},{"text":"?, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLibObject"}],"role":"symbol","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","extendedModule":"GLibObject","roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and another reference is established."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"references":{"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject","abstract":[],"role":"collection","kind":"symbol","title":"GLibObject","type":"topic"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","title":"SignalGroupRef","abstract":[{"code":"GSignalGroup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" manages a collection of signals on a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GObject"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SignalGroupRef"}],"fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SignalGroupRef","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref"},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef/addToggleRef(notify:data:)":{"abstract":[{"text":"Increases the reference count of the object by one and sets a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"callback to be called when all other references to the object are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dropped, or when this is already the last reference to the object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and another reference is established.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/addtoggleref(notify:data:)","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/addToggleRef(notify:data:)","role":"symbol","title":"addToggleRef(notify:data:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"addToggleRef","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"notify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"GToggleNotify","preciseIdentifier":"c:gobject.h@T@GToggleNotify","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?, "},{"text":"data","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"gpointer","preciseIdentifier":"c:gtypes.h@T@gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?)","kind":"text"}]},"doc://GLibObject/documentation/GLibObject/SignalGroupRef/ObjectProtocol-Implementations":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLibObject\/documentation\/GLibObject\/SignalGroupRef\/ObjectProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","kind":"article","title":"ObjectProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glibobject\/signalgroupref\/objectprotocol-implementations"}}}